author: Nick Castillo
title: Longhorns legend Vince Young upholds bet, sports Cal jersey after Texas' 45-44 loss
text:
Vince Young kept his bet after the Longhorns lost to California, 45-44 on Saturday.
After making a bet with Texas high school football coach Scott X. Nady, a former California players, Young had to wear a Golden Bears' t-shirt jersey.
The original bet:
Sept. 19th CAL vs. Texas! Loser goes on TV in other schools shirt! VY is going to look GREAT in Blue & Gold! Go Bears pic.twitter.com/pkRAyFDZAo
— Scott X. Nady (@CoachNady) July 30, 2015 Young gets his jersey:
The shirt has been delivered.... What he chooses to do with it is up to him! GO BEARS!!!! pic.twitter.com/UiBgZbKCSe
— Scott X. Nady (@CoachNady) September 20, 2015 Young with the jersey:
Front & Back VY is a Stand up guy! @JaredGoff16 @CALCoachDykes @CalCoachKaufman @coachtf @CalFootball @ @CalAthletics pic.twitter.com/YmDeSplJAD
— Scott X. Nady (@CoachNady) September 20, 2015 On Twitter:
 @Nick_Castillo74
